edu.mines.jtk.util
Interface Float4

public interface Float4

A generic interface for a 4-D array of floats. This interface enables getting and setting 1-, 2-, 3- and 4-D subarrays (slices) of elements from any data structure that can be indexed like a 4-D array. Unlike a 4-D array, that data structure need not reside entirely in memory.

Logically, the 4-D array can be considered as float a[n4][n3][n2][n1], where n1 is the fastest array dimension, and n4 is the slowest.

Version:
2012.05.28
Author:
Dave Hale, Colorado School of Mines
